### Content Sampling

For each workspace, extract representative samples:

```rust
fn extract_samples(hits: &[SearchHit], workspace: &str) -> Vec<String> {
    let workspace_hits: Vec<_> = hits.iter()
        .filter(|h| h.workspace == workspace)
        .collect();

    // Take first 5 unique titles
    let mut titles: Vec<String> = workspace_hits.iter()
        .map(|h| h.title.clone())
        .collect::<HashSet<_>>()
        .into_iter()
        .take(5)
        .collect();

    titles.sort();
    titles
}
```

## Exclusion Capability

Users should be able to exclude content from the summary view:

```rust
pub struct ExclusionSet {
    pub excluded_workspaces: HashSet<String>,
    pub excluded_conversations: HashSet<String>,
    pub excluded_patterns: Vec<Regex>,  // Exclude by title pattern
}

impl ExclusionSet {
    pub fn apply(&self, hits: &[SearchHit]) -> Vec<SearchHit> {
        hits.iter()
            .filter(|h| \!self.excluded_workspaces.contains(&h.workspace))
            .filter(|h| \!h.conversation_id.as_ref()
                .map(|id| self.excluded_conversations.contains(id))
                .unwrap_or(false))
            .filter(|h| \!self.excluded_patterns.iter()
                .any(|p| p.is_match(&h.title)))
            .cloned()
            .collect()
    }
}
```

